WEBVTT

00:02.107 --> 00:04.065
is gonna have to
get through them.

00:04.109 --> 00:05.501
[Walkers growling]

00:05.545 --> 00:08.287
Morgan Jones?I'm not worried about him.

00:08.330 --> 00:09.462
[ Explosion in distance ]

00:09.505 --> 00:11.768
The warheads
are separating.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.596
I'm sorry it has to
end this way.

00:13.640 --> 00:14.771
[Baby crying]

00:14.815 --> 00:16.556
I can hear her,
Morgan.

00:16.599 --> 00:19.385
[Baby crying continues]

00:19.428 --> 00:21.082
Oh, it's alright.

00:21.126 --> 00:24.477
[Explosion]

00:24.520 --> 00:25.869
Go.

00:25.913 --> 00:28.655
Go, go!

00:29.960 --> 00:31.875
[Mo crying]

00:36.271 --> 00:46.238
♪

00:46.281 --> 00:51.243
[Crying continues]

00:51.286 --> 01:01.253
♪

01:01.296 --> 01:06.258
[Crying continues]

01:10.262 --> 01:11.654
[Sighs]

01:11.698 --> 01:13.178
Grace:
Didn't she just go to sleep?

01:13.221 --> 01:15.136
Think so.

01:15.180 --> 01:19.227
[Crying continues]

01:21.708 --> 01:23.579
[Rufus whines]

01:25.451 --> 01:27.627
Let's go.

01:27.670 --> 01:29.846
You're good.

01:29.890 --> 01:32.066
I know, baby.

01:32.110 --> 01:34.329
I know, I know.
Shh.

01:34.373 --> 01:36.679
It's alright.
You're doing great.

01:36.723 --> 01:37.811
There you go.

01:37.854 --> 01:40.161
Come here.
Come here.

01:40.205 --> 01:41.293
You're doing good.

01:43.295 --> 01:45.166
It's alright.

01:45.210 --> 01:47.473
It's alright. I got you.

01:47.516 --> 01:49.039
[Crying continues]

01:49.083 --> 01:50.215
What's wrong?

01:50.258 --> 01:52.173
It's the same as last time,
alright?

01:52.217 --> 01:53.218
She's hungry.

01:56.221 --> 01:58.005
[Crying fades]

01:58.048 --> 02:00.921
[Wind howling, metallic
creaking]

02:10.757 --> 02:13.325
[Mask hissing]

02:56.846 --> 02:59.675
[Walker growling]

03:30.315 --> 03:31.794
[Door bell jingles]

03:31.838 --> 03:34.232
[Geiger counter ticking]

03:38.758 --> 03:40.760
[Rat squeaking]

03:42.979 --> 03:44.894
Anyone there?

04:00.258 --> 04:01.302
[Banging in distance]

04:01.346 --> 04:03.435
I said, anyone there?!

04:18.363 --> 04:19.929
Shoo.

04:19.973 --> 04:21.366
Aw, shit.

04:28.373 --> 04:30.113
Oh, God.

04:35.423 --> 04:37.773
[Door opens in distance]

04:39.166 --> 04:42.474
[Shelf clatters]

04:42.517 --> 04:44.171
Man: You hear that?

04:45.868 --> 04:47.000
What is it?

04:47.043 --> 04:52.310
♪

04:52.353 --> 04:53.920
I don't know.
Over here!

04:53.963 --> 04:59.404
♪

04:59.447 --> 05:02.276
[Man breathing heavily]

05:02.320 --> 05:09.283
♪

05:09.327 --> 05:16.246
♪

05:16.290 --> 05:17.639
[Man grunts]

05:17.683 --> 05:18.727
[Rat squealing]

05:18.771 --> 05:19.815
Woman: Aah!

05:19.859 --> 05:22.775
Oh!
[Gasps]

05:22.818 --> 05:25.821
Fred,
it's just a damn rat.

05:25.865 --> 05:28.302
Ah, shit.
I clipped it.

05:28.346 --> 05:31.305
♪

05:31.349 --> 05:32.785
Come on.
Let's go.

05:32.828 --> 05:36.528
♪

05:36.571 --> 05:38.921
[Door opens, bell jingles]

05:38.965 --> 05:41.446
[Door closes, bell jingles]

05:41.489 --> 05:48.191
♪

05:48.235 --> 05:54.894
♪

05:54.937 --> 06:01.727
♪

06:09.212 --> 06:12.215
[Geiger counter ticking]

06:15.218 --> 06:16.829
Damn it.

06:16.872 --> 06:19.353
♪

06:19.397 --> 06:21.529
[Grunts]

06:21.573 --> 06:24.314
I'm right here!

06:24.358 --> 06:26.055
I said I'm right here!

06:26.099 --> 06:27.056
[Door opens, bell jingles]

06:27.100 --> 06:29.450
[Walker growling]

06:29.494 --> 06:31.844
Didn't you hear me?!

06:31.887 --> 06:39.765
♪

06:39.808 --> 06:43.421
[Chuckles]

06:43.464 --> 06:46.989
You can rob me!

06:47.033 --> 06:50.079
You can take everything from me!

06:50.123 --> 06:53.866
[Sobbing]

06:53.909 --> 07:02.483
♪

07:02.527 --> 07:06.182
I mean it!!

07:06.226 --> 07:08.794
I don't even want to be here!

07:08.837 --> 07:13.102
♪

07:13.146 --> 07:16.541
[Sobbing]

07:16.584 --> 07:20.327
I don't want to be here anymore!

07:29.641 --> 07:33.253
[Walker growling]

07:46.614 --> 07:54.013
♪

07:54.056 --> 08:01.499
♪

08:04.023 --> 08:05.807
[Crying]

08:05.851 --> 08:08.549
Morgan: Come on. You don't
want to try some of this?

08:08.593 --> 08:10.551
No? Okay.

08:10.595 --> 08:13.423
I don't know.
She ain't gonna eat it.

08:13.467 --> 08:14.947
If she's hungry,
she will.

08:14.990 --> 08:16.862
She's not ready
for solids.

08:16.905 --> 08:23.564
[Crying continues]

08:23.608 --> 08:26.132
Alright, so it's my turn
to go out.

08:26.175 --> 08:27.699
Maybe I'll have
better luck.

08:27.742 --> 08:29.701
No.
No, I'll go.

08:29.744 --> 08:31.398
Hey, wait.
Stop. What?

08:31.441 --> 08:33.095
Stop.

08:33.139 --> 08:35.054
There's a reason
why there's a limit.

08:35.097 --> 08:37.360
You were exposed once
before all this.

08:37.404 --> 08:40.755
I know.And we talked about the fallout
and the weather patterns and --

08:40.799 --> 08:43.105
and the readings you were
getting, and you said six hours.

08:43.149 --> 08:44.411
That was you.

08:44.454 --> 08:45.804
You said six hours
is the longest

08:45.847 --> 08:46.979
that either one of us
could be out there.

08:47.022 --> 08:48.546
You said that, right?

08:51.766 --> 08:53.420
Yeah.

08:53.463 --> 08:55.727
Then it's my turn,
Grace.

08:58.425 --> 09:01.080
And I'll be back
before the clock hits zero.

09:01.123 --> 09:04.518
[Crying continues]

09:04.562 --> 09:06.694
You'll be fine.

09:06.738 --> 09:08.261
Maybe sing to her.

09:08.304 --> 09:12.047
That used to
soothe Duane.

09:12.091 --> 09:15.398
Oh. Okay.

09:15.442 --> 09:18.401
[Crying continues]

09:18.445 --> 09:21.056
[Keys jangling]

09:23.798 --> 09:26.105
[Crying continues]

09:30.109 --> 09:33.678
Okay. Please, just --
just for a little bit.

09:33.721 --> 09:35.114
Just for a little bit.

09:35.157 --> 09:40.119
[Crying continues]

09:40.162 --> 09:41.990
Please, please,
just for a little bit!

09:42.034 --> 09:44.384
Please, just for a little bit.

09:44.427 --> 09:46.560
Oh, God.

09:46.604 --> 09:47.648
Okay.

09:47.692 --> 09:51.652
[Crying continues]

09:51.696 --> 09:54.394
Okay. I know.

09:54.437 --> 09:55.438
I know.

09:55.482 --> 09:57.266
I know.

09:58.833 --> 10:02.532
[Crying continues]

10:02.576 --> 10:04.709
I know. I know.
It's not fair.

10:04.752 --> 10:07.102
You didn't ask to be here,
and neither did I.

10:07.146 --> 10:10.410
I know. I know.

10:10.453 --> 10:12.934
I know.

10:12.978 --> 10:17.417
[Crying continues]

10:17.460 --> 10:19.201
[Sobbing]
I know what he said.

10:19.245 --> 10:21.682
I know what he said,
but I can't.

10:21.726 --> 10:23.684
I can't sing to you.

10:23.728 --> 10:25.643
I'm sorry. I can't.

10:31.953 --> 10:35.653
[ "Baby Please Forgive Me"
playing]

10:35.696 --> 10:39.004
Please listen.

10:39.047 --> 10:41.093
Okay. Shh.

10:41.136 --> 10:43.965
It's alright. It's alright.
Okay.

10:44.009 --> 10:45.271
♪ No matter how hard I try♪There you go.

10:45.314 --> 10:47.403
[Crying stops]There you go. Good girl.

10:47.447 --> 10:49.101
Okay.

10:50.580 --> 10:53.627
♪ To make me forget you♪Thank you.

10:53.671 --> 10:56.543
♪

10:56.586 --> 11:00.765
♪ I can't get you off my mind♪

11:00.808 --> 11:03.463
♪

11:03.506 --> 11:06.640
♪ So, I'm always
feeling blue♪

11:06.684 --> 11:09.425
♪

11:09.469 --> 11:14.735
♪ Baby, please forgive me...♪

11:14.779 --> 11:16.432
[Music echoing, fading]

11:16.476 --> 11:20.828
♪ You know I love you so♪

11:20.872 --> 11:26.007
[ "Cabin On The Hill"playing]

11:26.051 --> 11:27.661
[Timer beeping]

11:27.705 --> 11:29.532
♪

11:29.576 --> 11:30.577
It's okay.

11:30.620 --> 11:31.752
Hey.

11:31.796 --> 11:34.973
It's just me.

11:35.016 --> 11:36.061
You were right.

11:38.019 --> 11:41.501
She likes music.[Chuckles]

11:41.544 --> 11:44.417
Did you find formula?

11:44.460 --> 11:46.724
No.

11:46.767 --> 11:49.509
But I'll be honest,
I didn't really look for it.

11:49.552 --> 11:52.338
I've been working
on something else instead.

11:52.381 --> 11:53.905
What?

11:56.690 --> 11:59.171
[Crying]

11:59.214 --> 12:00.912
This is
our way out of here.

12:03.653 --> 12:04.742
You serious?

12:04.785 --> 12:07.092
It is safe for all of us.

12:07.135 --> 12:09.094
I made sure of it.

12:09.137 --> 12:11.139
I made this out of a smock

12:11.183 --> 12:14.273
I found
in the ship's dental kit.

12:14.316 --> 12:17.624
It'll protect her from
the background radiation.

12:17.667 --> 12:19.234
It's alright.

12:19.278 --> 12:21.410
It's okay.

12:21.454 --> 12:22.803
Be good.

12:22.847 --> 12:25.501
[Crying continues]

12:25.545 --> 12:28.156
And the air --
the air inside here

12:28.200 --> 12:30.898
is as clean
as it is inside the sub.

12:33.945 --> 12:36.077
We should get in.

12:36.121 --> 12:38.384
We know the number of warheads
on that missile --

12:38.427 --> 12:40.081
how they spread out,
their yield,

12:40.125 --> 12:42.823
and that the fallout
will probably cover

12:42.867 --> 12:45.434
a couple hundred miles in any
direction, but with the fuel

12:45.478 --> 12:48.089
I got from the sub's diesels,
we can make it out.

12:48.133 --> 12:50.918
It's too far.
It'll take too long.I can get as far as need to get
in less than six hours,

12:50.962 --> 12:53.138
even if some of the roads
are busted up.We don't even know
what it's like out there.

12:53.181 --> 12:55.749
I have stripped this thing of
everything we don't need, Grace.Morgan --

12:55.793 --> 12:57.795
It is light
and it is fast.

13:01.233 --> 13:02.974
Why are you doing this?

13:05.933 --> 13:08.414
This is not
what you wanted.

13:08.457 --> 13:11.286
I know it,
and it's no place for a baby.

13:11.330 --> 13:13.419
So, we should go.

13:13.462 --> 13:16.683
We can build something someplace
else that would actually last.

13:22.210 --> 13:24.517
You're doing this for me?

13:24.560 --> 13:26.127
And for Mo.

13:29.174 --> 13:30.828
Hey.

13:34.135 --> 13:35.876
You can even
pick the music.

13:35.920 --> 13:38.487
It's a road trip,
right?

13:38.531 --> 13:39.837
And it'll
keep Mo sleeping.

13:46.669 --> 13:48.367
[Engine starts]

13:48.410 --> 13:50.978
[ "I'll Put That Gambling Down"
playing]

13:51.022 --> 13:57.115
♪

13:57.158 --> 14:03.164
♪

14:03.208 --> 14:05.732
[ "Untie The Ribbon"playing]

14:05.775 --> 14:14.349
♪

14:14.393 --> 14:19.180
♪ I'm standing in the glow♪

14:19.224 --> 14:23.271
♪ Of the bridges I have burned♪

14:23.315 --> 14:25.970
It's a lot worse
than I thought.

14:26.013 --> 14:28.842
The bombs detonated
on the ground.

14:28.886 --> 14:32.150
If they didn't burn clean,

14:32.193 --> 14:33.847
there could be a lot
of dangerous stuff out here

14:33.891 --> 14:36.023
that'll stick around
for a long time.

14:36.067 --> 14:38.025
It's a good thing
we're getting out of here.

14:38.069 --> 14:40.375
The really dangerous stuff --
you can't see it.

14:40.419 --> 14:42.900
This won't even pick it up.

14:42.943 --> 14:45.554
It's gonna get a lot worse
before it gets better, Morgan.

14:45.598 --> 14:47.208
We're heading
in the right direction.

14:47.252 --> 14:48.731
That's what matters.That's what I'm trying
to tell you.

14:48.775 --> 14:51.430
You don't know that.Well, I...

14:51.473 --> 14:54.259
I feel it.

14:54.302 --> 14:57.001
Everything I've been through and
everything you've been through.

14:57.044 --> 14:58.828
Ain't we due a break?

14:58.872 --> 15:02.310
[Geiger counter ticking]

15:02.354 --> 15:04.530
♪ It's a game no one can win♪

15:04.573 --> 15:07.533
We okay?

15:07.576 --> 15:09.927
We're a lot closer to ground
zero than I thought.

15:09.970 --> 15:13.017
You certain we're
on the right road?

15:13.060 --> 15:14.496
Yeah.

15:14.540 --> 15:16.281
That town up ahead's
on the map.

15:17.935 --> 15:21.590
[Walker growling]

15:35.430 --> 15:38.085
♪ Untie the ribbon♪

15:38.129 --> 15:41.045
Maybe things are gonna get worse
before they get better.

15:41.088 --> 15:44.004
Morgan, we need to talk.About what?

15:44.048 --> 15:45.788
About what happens
when we get...

15:45.832 --> 15:47.486
wherever we get.

15:47.529 --> 15:49.357
What do you mean
"what happens"?

15:49.401 --> 15:51.794
Grace: There's a playlist of
songs I left on this tape.

15:51.838 --> 15:54.797
What is this? I hope you listen to them...

15:54.841 --> 15:57.278
No. ...they'll make you smile.

15:57.322 --> 15:58.888
Turn it off.
I didn't know
this was on there.

15:58.932 --> 16:00.151
Morgan, make it stop.Okay.

16:00.194 --> 16:01.761
Turn it --
I'm trying.

16:01.804 --> 16:03.371
Stop it right now!
Turn it off!
I'm trying.

16:03.415 --> 16:06.200
Morgan, please stop it!

16:06.244 --> 16:07.810
[ "In Dreams"playing]I don't want to hear
that song!

16:07.854 --> 16:09.029
Turn it off!

16:09.073 --> 16:10.639
[Mo crying]

16:10.683 --> 16:11.684
Morgan!

16:11.727 --> 16:12.990
Ah!

16:13.033 --> 16:16.950
[Tires squealing]

16:16.994 --> 16:22.042
♪

16:22.086 --> 16:26.525
♪ I close my eyes♪

16:26.568 --> 16:31.095
♪ Then I drift away♪

16:31.138 --> 16:33.227
♪ Into the magic night♪[Crying continues]

16:33.271 --> 16:34.315
♪ I softly --♪[Breathlessly] Stop it.

16:34.359 --> 16:36.839
Stop it!

16:36.883 --> 16:38.580
[Music stops]Stop it, Morgan!

16:38.624 --> 16:40.104
It's out. It's out.

16:40.147 --> 16:42.802
It's out.
[Sobbing]
I don't want to hear it!

16:42.845 --> 16:46.501
I don't want to hear it!
Make it stop!

16:57.077 --> 17:00.037
Morgan:
Ah, the wheel's bent.

17:00.080 --> 17:01.821
Can't drive on it.

17:01.864 --> 17:03.692
Can you fix it?

17:03.736 --> 17:07.218
Thought I saw a body shop
back there.

17:07.261 --> 17:08.697
How much time do you need?

17:08.741 --> 17:10.351
How much time can we spare?

17:13.963 --> 17:15.182
30 minutes.

17:15.226 --> 17:17.576
We better move.

17:17.619 --> 17:21.232
[Crying continues]

17:25.149 --> 17:26.628
Hey.

17:26.672 --> 17:29.544
Hey, what the hell
are you doing?

17:29.588 --> 17:32.721
Once you fix the car,
you take the baby and you go.

17:32.765 --> 17:34.593
What?The car will be lighter.

17:34.636 --> 17:36.247
You'll get farther.

17:36.290 --> 17:37.770
The rations will
last you longer.

17:37.813 --> 17:39.380
You don't have to do this.The clock is ticking.

17:39.424 --> 17:41.121
None of that will make enough
of a difference.

17:41.165 --> 17:43.254
I'll get the shop open
and you can move the car.

17:43.297 --> 17:45.212
Oh, come on.
Put your mask back on, please.

17:45.256 --> 17:46.213
No, there's no --Put it on. Put it on.

17:46.257 --> 17:48.650
There's no time to argue!

17:48.694 --> 17:51.000
You and the baby need
every second you can get.

17:51.044 --> 17:52.306
What we need is you.

17:52.350 --> 17:55.309
That's not true,
Morgan.

17:55.353 --> 18:00.053
You've been doing all the heavy
lifting on your own already.

18:00.097 --> 18:01.707
You'll die.
I know.

18:04.405 --> 18:07.234
And I'm okay with that.

18:07.278 --> 18:09.018
You're okay with it?

18:09.062 --> 18:11.630
I didn't want any of this,
Morgan.

18:11.673 --> 18:14.023
I knew what it was
gonna be like.

18:14.067 --> 18:16.156
I knew how hard
it would be,

18:16.200 --> 18:18.245
how it would all probably end
in the same place,

18:18.289 --> 18:21.640
but take longer and be
a hell of a lot more painful.

18:21.683 --> 18:24.947
We heard Mo crying.
We had to go to her.

18:24.991 --> 18:26.253
We have to
take care of her.

18:26.297 --> 18:28.299
You decided that.

18:28.342 --> 18:30.127
You put the gun down
and now you have to live

18:30.170 --> 18:31.780
with that decision,
but I don't.

18:31.824 --> 18:39.962
♪

18:40.006 --> 18:43.183
I'm sorry, Morgan,
but I can't --
Hey.

18:43.227 --> 18:44.750
I can't --Just put the mask on.

18:44.793 --> 18:46.186
I can't do this,
and I don't have it in me.

18:46.230 --> 18:48.145
[Gun cocks]

18:48.188 --> 18:52.105
Sorry to interrupt the quarrel.

18:52.149 --> 18:55.978
But we don't really have time
for that shit.

18:56.022 --> 18:58.329
Careful, Bea![Rufus barks, Mo crying]

18:58.372 --> 19:00.113
Hey, don't.

19:00.157 --> 19:01.462
Rufus.

19:01.506 --> 19:02.942
Bea: Where is she?Rufus, come back!

19:02.985 --> 19:05.205
If you're smart,
you'll do the same.

19:05.249 --> 19:06.859
I hear her.

19:06.902 --> 19:11.255
[Mo crying]

19:11.298 --> 19:13.866
They've got her.
She's here.

19:13.909 --> 19:15.781
Oh, hi. Hi, baby.

19:15.824 --> 19:18.305
Hey, you stay
away from her.

19:18.349 --> 19:20.394
Look, if you want this car,
you can take it.

19:20.438 --> 19:22.962
It's just that Mo,
our little baby, she's inside,

19:23.005 --> 19:25.269
and we just want to
take her someplace safe.

19:25.312 --> 19:26.661
Mo?

19:26.705 --> 19:28.228
Her name's Emma.

19:28.272 --> 19:29.925
And she's not your baby.

19:29.969 --> 19:31.057
She's ours.

19:31.100 --> 19:32.798
[Crying continues]

19:32.841 --> 19:36.062
♪

19:36.105 --> 19:38.456
Mommy's here.
Mommy's here.

19:38.499 --> 19:41.372
♪

19:45.114 --> 19:48.770
[Mo crying]

19:48.814 --> 19:52.296
[Groans]
Did you even feed my baby?

19:52.339 --> 19:54.472
[Geiger counter ticking]

19:54.515 --> 20:01.435
♪

20:01.479 --> 20:03.220
We shouldn't get close.

20:03.263 --> 20:05.004
I think
those are Beta burns.

20:05.047 --> 20:07.746
They may have been exposed
to worse stuff, too.

20:07.789 --> 20:10.052
Okay.

20:12.054 --> 20:14.056
What's with the bandages?

20:14.100 --> 20:16.145
Are you hurt?

20:16.189 --> 20:17.973
Were you close to the blast?

20:18.017 --> 20:19.671
Just change the tire.

20:22.674 --> 20:25.459
See, I have to protect
that child,

20:25.503 --> 20:27.374
and it doesn't matter
whose kid you think she is.

20:27.418 --> 20:29.420
Are you hearing
the clicking?

20:29.463 --> 20:32.379
Wasn't going that fast
'til you two showed up.

20:32.423 --> 20:33.598
You wanna help?

20:33.641 --> 20:35.077
Fix the damn tire.

20:35.121 --> 20:37.123
[Crying continues]

20:37.166 --> 20:38.559
Fred, come help me.

20:41.083 --> 20:42.911
I can get us out of this.He'll shoot you.

20:42.955 --> 20:44.696
No, I can stop him before.

20:44.739 --> 20:47.873
Shh.
Please, please, be quiet.

20:47.916 --> 20:49.353
Shh. I know.
I know, I know.

20:49.396 --> 20:51.311
It's okay.
It's okay.

20:51.355 --> 20:53.139
Exactly what are they
exposing her to?

20:53.182 --> 20:55.446
Depends where they've been.

20:55.489 --> 20:57.883
Right now, I'm more worried
about this running out.

20:57.926 --> 21:00.886
She can survive them.
She can't survive this.

21:00.929 --> 21:02.366
We fix the car, make sure

21:02.409 --> 21:04.716
that we have everything we need,
then we move.

21:04.759 --> 21:07.240
Okay.
This won't take long.

21:07.284 --> 21:10.765
♪

21:10.809 --> 21:12.811
I meant
what I said before.

21:12.854 --> 21:15.596
I may not want to be here,
but I'm not giving up now.

21:15.640 --> 21:17.424
Not like this.
Not with them.

21:17.468 --> 21:21.689
Not when I know you and Mo
could end up dead, too.

21:21.733 --> 21:24.039
You mean that?
I do.

21:24.083 --> 21:26.346
But I'm still here.

21:26.390 --> 21:27.956
I'm not with the person
I really want to be with.

21:28.000 --> 21:29.610
You mean Athena?

21:32.831 --> 21:34.485
I'm never gonna apologize
for giving you

21:34.528 --> 21:37.270
and that baby another day.

21:37.314 --> 21:40.578
Did you really think that we can
be some kind of family with Mo?

21:40.621 --> 21:42.275
I can't do that.
It won't be the same.

21:42.319 --> 21:43.276
Doesn't mean it won't
be something.

21:43.320 --> 21:44.625
[Garage door thumping]

21:44.669 --> 21:48.368
[Walkers growling]

21:48.412 --> 21:50.414
Fred: Bea, you gotta
keep her quiet.

21:50.457 --> 21:53.721
Shh, shh. Shh, shh, shh.
Please, be quiet.

21:53.765 --> 21:55.244
Please, please, please.Bea.

21:55.288 --> 21:57.377
I know, Fred, I'm trying.You got to stop her.

21:57.421 --> 21:59.248
I'm trying.
Hurry up!

21:59.292 --> 22:01.207
I'm going as fast as I can.

22:01.250 --> 22:02.991
Shut her up!
I'm trying!

22:03.035 --> 22:05.211
You remember what happened
last time?

22:05.254 --> 22:06.430
Shoot them!

22:06.473 --> 22:07.474
That'll just draw more.

22:07.518 --> 22:10.085
[Walkers growling]

22:10.129 --> 22:12.914
Grace, get the tape.

22:12.958 --> 22:14.786
Shh. Shh. Shh.

22:14.829 --> 22:16.091
[Whimpers][Crying continues]

22:16.135 --> 22:19.965
[Growling continues]

22:20.008 --> 22:24.839
♪

22:24.883 --> 22:26.580
What happened
to those walkers?

22:26.624 --> 22:29.627
They're from the crater.
Be careful.

22:29.670 --> 22:31.280
They fall apart
when you hit 'em,

22:31.324 --> 22:33.152
and you don't want them
to fall apart on you.

22:33.195 --> 22:36.721
Shh. Shh.
Shh. Shh.

22:36.764 --> 22:38.592
[Music playing indistinctly]

22:38.636 --> 22:40.377
She likes it.

22:40.420 --> 22:41.856
Trust me.

22:41.900 --> 22:44.642
[Crying stops]

22:44.685 --> 22:49.211
♪

22:49.255 --> 22:50.822
How'd you know?

22:50.865 --> 23:00.440
♪

23:00.484 --> 23:03.269
Morgan: Door's rotted.
It's not gonna hold.

23:03.312 --> 23:05.924
It'll hold, as long
as more don't show up.

23:05.967 --> 23:08.579
♪

23:08.622 --> 23:11.582
What's your name?

23:11.625 --> 23:13.627
I helped you, didn't I?

23:13.671 --> 23:16.195
I want what's best
for her, too.

23:18.284 --> 23:19.459
I'm Bea.

23:19.503 --> 23:22.462
Alright, Bea.
I'm Grace.

23:22.506 --> 23:24.638
And that's Morgan.

23:24.682 --> 23:26.945
My husband --
he's called Fred.

23:26.988 --> 23:31.123
Bea, this ain't a potluck
in the church basement!

23:31.166 --> 23:33.125
Are you from this town?

23:33.168 --> 23:35.257
Did you live here?

23:35.301 --> 23:37.477
Across the street.
In the old honky tonk.

23:37.521 --> 23:38.870
Were there
others with you?

23:38.913 --> 23:41.002
People lived in
all these buildings.

23:41.046 --> 23:44.919
Ones connected by the strings.
It's how we talked.

23:44.963 --> 23:46.704
Wrap it up, Bea.

23:46.747 --> 23:48.923
The dead ain't known
for their patience.

23:48.967 --> 23:51.360
We need to leave.
[Sniffles]

23:51.404 --> 23:54.320
For her.
[Grunts]

23:54.363 --> 23:55.713
It's not safe here.

23:55.756 --> 23:57.541
We know.

23:57.584 --> 24:00.195
I wasn't lying when I said
we want what's best for her.

24:00.239 --> 24:02.459
We can --
We can fit in the car.

24:02.502 --> 24:04.591
We can all leave together.

24:04.635 --> 24:07.594
She's right.
We know the way out of here.

24:07.638 --> 24:09.466
We know a safe path
we can take.

24:09.509 --> 24:12.904
You know about Padre,
too?

24:12.947 --> 24:16.560
What's Padre?Be quiet, Bea.

24:16.603 --> 24:18.170
Your daughter could
still be out there.

24:18.213 --> 24:19.867
You could still find her.

24:19.911 --> 24:21.913
She may need you,
and we can --

24:21.956 --> 24:25.003
we can help because
the car's ready to go.

24:25.046 --> 24:26.308
Fred: Bea.

24:26.352 --> 24:27.962
Put her things in the car
and get in.

24:28.006 --> 24:29.355
♪

24:29.398 --> 24:31.400
[Mo fussing]

24:31.444 --> 24:35.187
[Mo crying]

24:35.230 --> 24:38.973
♪

24:39.017 --> 24:40.888
Against the wall.

24:40.932 --> 24:42.194
Back up.

24:42.237 --> 24:43.282
You did this, right?

24:43.325 --> 24:44.892
I wouldn't endanger her.

24:44.936 --> 24:46.677
Much obliged.

24:46.720 --> 24:48.940
We'll never forget how you folks
helped our family.

24:48.983 --> 24:51.116
But the masks -- can we at least
get them back

24:51.159 --> 24:54.511
if you're gonna leave us
stranded here?

24:54.554 --> 24:59.472
♪

24:59.516 --> 25:01.561
Aah!

25:01.605 --> 25:03.128
[Gun cocks]

25:03.171 --> 25:04.695
[Engine starts]

25:04.738 --> 25:07.088
Don't![Gunshot fires]

25:07.132 --> 25:10.135
You damage the car,
no one leaves.

25:10.178 --> 25:13.617
♪

25:13.660 --> 25:16.228
They might be able
to get her someplace safe.This isn't about her.

25:16.271 --> 25:18.186
This is about you,
because you're scared.

25:18.230 --> 25:21.320
[Tires squealing]

25:21.363 --> 25:23.278
Already lost one child.

25:23.322 --> 25:25.193
Not gonna
let that happen again.

25:25.237 --> 25:27.544
[Gunshot fires]

25:27.587 --> 25:28.980
I lost a child, too!

25:29.023 --> 25:30.982
Then you know why
I have to do this!

25:31.025 --> 25:35.987
♪

25:36.030 --> 25:37.379
Morgan!

25:37.423 --> 25:39.425
♪

25:39.468 --> 25:41.819
[Mo crying]

25:41.862 --> 25:43.560
Out!

25:45.257 --> 25:46.867
[Groans]

25:46.911 --> 25:51.872
[Crying continues]

25:51.916 --> 25:54.919
[Both grunting]

25:54.962 --> 25:57.399
Grace!
Don't let Mo out of your sight!

25:57.443 --> 26:03.014
♪

26:03.057 --> 26:08.628
♪

26:08.672 --> 26:10.891
I'm not one of them.

26:10.935 --> 26:12.110
Not yet.

26:12.153 --> 26:14.852
[Walkers growling]

26:14.895 --> 26:16.593
Let's keep it that way.

26:16.636 --> 26:17.898
Come on.

26:17.942 --> 26:18.899
Come on.

26:18.943 --> 26:20.422
♪

26:20.466 --> 26:22.076
Come on.

26:22.120 --> 26:26.428
♪

26:29.910 --> 26:33.958
[Walkers growling]

26:43.489 --> 26:45.012
How close were you
to the blast?

26:45.056 --> 26:48.494
A few miles.

26:48.537 --> 26:52.019
Is that how
you got those burns?No.

26:52.063 --> 26:55.762
We were in the root cellar
when the bombs went off.

26:55.806 --> 26:58.417
We got these...

26:58.460 --> 27:00.071
later.

27:05.685 --> 27:08.166
I know -- I know we don't have
much time left.

27:08.209 --> 27:12.300
I-I just want to get Emma
someplace safe before the end.

27:12.344 --> 27:16.391
I've been
in your shoes before.

27:16.435 --> 27:19.699
Still am in some ways.

27:19.743 --> 27:22.049
It's why I'm telling you
she is not your child to take.

27:22.093 --> 27:23.442
[Music playing indistinctly]She's not yours, either.

27:23.485 --> 27:25.183
Not by blood, but I made
her father a promise

27:25.226 --> 27:28.403
that I would build
a better world for her.

27:28.447 --> 27:30.101
Least I can do
is take her someplace

27:30.144 --> 27:32.407
where
that might be possible.

27:32.451 --> 27:35.497
I knew that you were taking her
someplace safe.

27:35.541 --> 27:37.151
If the only way that I could
get her back

27:37.195 --> 27:39.153
was to keep her
from getting to that place,

27:39.197 --> 27:42.896
I'd let you take her.Yeah, but that's not
what happened back there.

27:42.940 --> 27:44.724
Where were you
taking her?

27:44.768 --> 27:46.813
We're taking her
outside the fallout.

27:46.857 --> 27:49.294
Fred: We tried doing
what you were doing.

27:49.337 --> 27:52.036
There was a storm
after the bomb went off.

27:52.079 --> 27:55.517
Pushed all that stuff in the
air clear toward Louisiana.

27:55.561 --> 27:57.128
So, we scrounged up
enough gas

27:57.171 --> 27:58.912
that still burned
to make the trip.

27:58.956 --> 28:01.828
Least we thought
it was enough.

28:01.872 --> 28:04.570
How do you think
we ended up like this?

28:04.613 --> 28:08.792
You keep driving that way,
you'll end up just like us.

28:08.835 --> 28:11.229
So, where were you trying
to take her just now?

28:15.320 --> 28:16.974
I'll show you.

28:17.017 --> 28:18.410
There.

28:18.453 --> 28:19.759
There it is.

28:19.803 --> 28:21.326
What is it?

28:21.369 --> 28:22.936
We know it's safe.

28:22.980 --> 28:24.372
We know
it's better than here.

28:24.416 --> 28:25.896
How?

28:27.245 --> 28:28.942
They don't want
anyone saying.

28:28.986 --> 28:30.770
Who doesn't?People on the radio.

28:30.814 --> 28:33.425
And you're sure
this is where it is?

28:33.468 --> 28:35.427
If you don't tell us, how can
we help you get there?

28:35.470 --> 28:37.646
We know where it's not.

28:37.690 --> 28:39.605
And there's only one
more direction to go looking.

28:39.648 --> 28:41.955
Searching like that, you're
gonna get yourself killed.

28:41.999 --> 28:43.391
[Scoffs]
It's too late for that.

28:43.435 --> 28:45.045
You're gonna get herkilled.

28:45.089 --> 28:50.485
I would never do that
to her.

28:50.529 --> 28:53.401
Morgan and I --
we have a place.

28:53.445 --> 28:54.794
It's not much,

28:54.838 --> 28:57.057
but it's protected
from everything out here.

28:57.101 --> 28:59.494
We had to leave because
we didn't have enough food.

28:59.538 --> 29:01.279
For her, for us.

29:01.322 --> 29:03.672
If you come back with us,
and bring some of those supplies

29:03.716 --> 29:05.674
you have here,
we could buy time.

29:05.718 --> 29:06.980
Does it look like
we have time?

29:07.024 --> 29:08.765
Shedoes.

29:08.808 --> 29:12.594
[Banging on door]

29:12.638 --> 29:14.422
We can't stay here
much longer.

29:14.466 --> 29:16.120
We need to
get back to the car.

29:16.163 --> 29:18.339
I'll fix the tire.
We'll get on the road.

29:18.383 --> 29:22.735
[Music stops, Mo crying]

29:22.779 --> 29:23.823
She's gonna draw more.

29:23.867 --> 29:25.607
The batteries.

29:25.651 --> 29:26.957
We need to get
to the car now.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.221
[Walkers growling]

29:30.264 --> 29:39.621
♪

29:39.665 --> 29:41.058
[Growling stops]

29:41.101 --> 29:50.371
♪

29:50.415 --> 29:52.765
How we doing?

29:52.809 --> 29:56.813
♪

29:56.856 --> 29:58.815
We've got to
go back to the sub.

29:58.858 --> 30:02.296
It's the only way to make sure
she stays safe.

30:02.340 --> 30:04.298
We've used
half the gas we had.

30:04.342 --> 30:08.085
It's pretty much
now or never.

30:08.128 --> 30:09.695
We just need to know
where we're going

30:09.738 --> 30:12.959
and what Padre actually is.

30:13.003 --> 30:15.744
What is Padre?

30:15.788 --> 30:17.050
What you said before,

30:17.094 --> 30:18.878
about me being scared,

30:18.922 --> 30:20.184
you're right.

30:20.227 --> 30:21.576
I am.

30:21.620 --> 30:22.882
But I'm not
the only one one.

30:22.926 --> 30:25.232
I'm doing the only thing
that we can.

30:25.276 --> 30:26.843
Because you're scared
of admitting

30:26.886 --> 30:29.367
what you wanted to build
for Mo might not be possible.

30:32.065 --> 30:34.067
Maybe you're right.

30:34.111 --> 30:35.460
But this thing
I wanted to build

30:35.503 --> 30:38.202
was just something close
to what I once had.

30:38.245 --> 30:39.681
I'm not even talking much.

30:39.725 --> 30:42.162
I'm talking about sitting at
a table with the woman

30:42.206 --> 30:45.078
I love, sharing a meal
and getting angry at our kid

30:45.122 --> 30:48.386
because he's reading comics
instead of talking to us.

30:48.429 --> 30:50.823
And I'm telling you
that might not be possible.

30:50.867 --> 30:54.827
♪

30:54.871 --> 30:57.656
I don't know what you
want me to do.

30:57.699 --> 31:00.224
Don't listen
to these people.

31:00.267 --> 31:02.095
Take her back to the sub.

31:02.139 --> 31:04.663
[Engine revving in distance]

31:04.706 --> 31:09.755
♪

31:09.798 --> 31:14.891
♪

31:14.934 --> 31:16.544
Shit.
Morgan?

31:18.068 --> 31:19.765
Grace:
Who the hell is that?

31:19.808 --> 31:21.854
Let's not find out.

31:21.898 --> 31:27.077
♪

31:30.994 --> 31:33.083
[Engine revving]

31:33.126 --> 31:35.041
Morgan.Get Mo inside.

31:35.085 --> 31:36.303
Keep her safe.

31:36.347 --> 31:38.958
You take cover
if you're staying.

31:39.002 --> 31:40.568
[Mo crying]

31:40.612 --> 31:46.923
♪

31:46.966 --> 31:51.057
[Walkers growling]

31:51.101 --> 31:53.712
Get in the back,
and keep her quiet.

31:53.755 --> 31:55.322
♪

31:55.366 --> 31:57.629
[Engine revs]

31:57.672 --> 32:03.852
♪

32:03.896 --> 32:06.594
[Car door opens]

32:06.638 --> 32:08.074
[Car door closes]

32:08.118 --> 32:17.910
♪

32:17.954 --> 32:20.130
Bea: Who -- Who is it?

32:20.173 --> 32:22.262
[Whimpering]

32:22.306 --> 32:25.222
[Crying continues]

32:25.265 --> 32:31.968
♪

32:32.011 --> 32:33.143
Morgan: Stop!

32:33.186 --> 32:35.841
[Gun cocks]

32:35.884 --> 32:38.409
Take another step
and I'll shoot.

32:38.452 --> 32:40.019
♪

32:40.063 --> 32:42.152
[Gunshot fires][Gasps]

32:42.195 --> 32:44.241
[Growling, crying continues]

32:44.284 --> 32:48.636
♪

32:48.680 --> 32:50.638
[Gunshot fires]

32:50.682 --> 32:52.292
[Gunshot fires]

32:52.336 --> 32:56.079
♪

32:56.122 --> 32:57.254
[Gunshot fires]

32:57.297 --> 32:58.777
Fred: Please be quiet.

32:58.820 --> 33:01.736
Please. Please. Shh.
Please. Please be quiet.

33:01.780 --> 33:04.087
Shh. Please, please, please.

33:04.130 --> 33:09.831
♪

33:09.875 --> 33:11.050
We gotta go back to Emma!

33:11.094 --> 33:13.574
[Scratching]

33:13.618 --> 33:15.141
Do you hear something?

33:15.185 --> 33:20.320
♪

33:20.364 --> 33:22.714
[Soft growling]

33:24.542 --> 33:26.718
The hell really happened
to your baby?

33:26.761 --> 33:30.809
♪

33:30.852 --> 33:34.682
[Crying continues]Please stop. Please stop.
Please stop.

33:34.726 --> 33:36.945
Please stop. Please stop.
Please stop crying!

33:36.989 --> 33:38.251
Stop crying.

33:38.295 --> 33:39.339
Please stop.

33:39.383 --> 33:41.167
Please.

33:41.211 --> 33:43.387
[Gunshot fires][Bea screams]

33:43.430 --> 33:47.826
Oh, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

33:47.869 --> 33:49.741
[Gunshot fires]

33:49.784 --> 33:51.569
[Sobbing]

33:51.612 --> 33:53.136
Bea.

33:53.179 --> 33:55.660
Bea.

33:55.703 --> 33:57.749
I'm sorry, but she
was already gone.

33:57.792 --> 34:00.969
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
She's not gone.

34:01.013 --> 34:02.449
She's inside with Fred.

34:02.493 --> 34:04.843
You know that's not her,
and it's okay to admit it,

34:04.886 --> 34:07.106
because that's how you start
saying goodbye

34:07.150 --> 34:10.936
and how stop repeating the same
mistakes over and over again.

34:10.979 --> 34:13.156
She was sick like us.
She was -- She was --

34:13.199 --> 34:15.375
She was not doing well.

34:15.419 --> 34:20.598
She was in pain,
and she started crying.

34:20.641 --> 34:22.252
She wouldn't stop.

34:22.295 --> 34:26.430
[Crying continues]

34:30.608 --> 34:31.739
What are you saying?

34:31.783 --> 34:34.525
Fred didn't want her
to suffer.

34:34.568 --> 34:36.875
Grace!

34:36.918 --> 34:38.181
Grace!

34:38.224 --> 34:39.921
♪

34:39.965 --> 34:41.140
[Gunshot fires]

34:41.184 --> 34:45.188
[Walkers growling,
gunshot fires]

34:45.231 --> 34:48.104
[Sobbing] I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, Emma.

34:48.147 --> 34:51.455
[Crying continues]

34:51.498 --> 34:54.284
♪

34:54.327 --> 34:56.242
[Trigger clicking]

34:56.286 --> 35:02.205
♪

35:02.248 --> 35:05.208
Grace, can you hear me?

35:05.251 --> 35:06.905
Grace!

35:06.948 --> 35:08.298
Grace, can you hear me?

35:08.341 --> 35:10.517
[Whimpers]

35:10.561 --> 35:12.476
It'll better this way.
I promise.

35:12.519 --> 35:15.218
Grace!
Grace, listen!

35:15.261 --> 35:16.393
Morgan?

35:16.436 --> 35:18.177
♪

35:18.221 --> 35:20.962
It'll be better. I promise.

35:21.006 --> 35:23.530
[Gunshot fires]

35:23.574 --> 35:28.796
[Growling continues]

35:28.840 --> 35:33.758
[Crying continues]

35:39.155 --> 35:41.635
Shh.

35:47.946 --> 35:51.645
[Crying, growling continues]

35:53.908 --> 35:57.521
[Distorted, echoing]
♪ ...like dreamers do♪

35:57.564 --> 36:00.741
♪ Then I fall asleep♪

36:00.785 --> 36:05.529
♪ To dreams, my dreams of you♪

36:08.140 --> 36:14.581
♪ In dreams,
I walk with you ♪

36:14.625 --> 36:16.844
[Crying, growling stops]

36:16.888 --> 36:23.677
♪ In dreams,
I talk with you ♪

36:25.940 --> 36:30.380
♪ In dreams, you're mine

36:33.165 --> 36:37.343
[Sniffles]
♪ All of the time

36:39.867 --> 36:47.310
♪ We're together in dreams

36:47.353 --> 36:50.443
♪ In dreams

36:50.487 --> 36:53.881
[Car horn blaring,
walkers growling]

36:56.667 --> 36:59.931
[Splattering]

37:02.716 --> 37:04.501
Okay.

37:04.544 --> 37:09.549
♪

37:09.593 --> 37:14.641
♪

37:14.685 --> 37:17.340
[Engine starts, vehicle departs]

37:17.383 --> 37:22.780
♪

37:22.823 --> 37:28.264
♪

37:31.789 --> 37:35.358
[ "It's Time To Quit Crying"
playing]

37:35.401 --> 37:40.972
♪

37:41.015 --> 37:46.543
♪

37:46.586 --> 37:50.111
Doesn't feel right,
leaving her behind.

37:50.155 --> 37:51.939
I get it.

37:51.983 --> 37:53.289
But she wants to
spend the time

37:53.332 --> 37:56.988
she has left
with her husband and child.

37:57.031 --> 38:01.949
♪

38:01.993 --> 38:04.169
I'm sorry, Grace.

38:04.212 --> 38:05.388
You don't have to say it.

38:05.431 --> 38:07.346
No, I almost
got her killed.

38:07.390 --> 38:10.654
You saved her.Only 'cause I was chasing
after what I needed.

38:10.697 --> 38:12.308
♪

38:12.351 --> 38:14.701
I should've
listened to you.

38:14.745 --> 38:17.791
I just wanted to give you
and her something more

38:17.835 --> 38:19.402
than what we have.

38:19.445 --> 38:22.622
♪

38:22.666 --> 38:25.016
You didn't fail her.

38:25.059 --> 38:26.670
You didn't fail me.

38:29.412 --> 38:32.328
But you would still rather die
than live out here with me.

38:32.371 --> 38:34.242
Not because of
what's out here.

38:34.286 --> 38:35.853
Not because of
anything you did.

38:41.424 --> 38:43.904
Maybe we're just
trying too hard.

38:43.948 --> 38:46.037
Reaching for too much.

38:46.080 --> 38:49.127
We are trying so hard
to fix ourselves,

38:49.170 --> 38:50.998
can't even recognize
that it might be alright

38:51.042 --> 38:52.826
just to be
a little bit broken.

38:52.870 --> 38:58.397
♪

38:58.441 --> 39:00.443
You're not replacing
Athena, Grace.

39:00.486 --> 39:03.141
♪

39:03.184 --> 39:04.534
You know that, right?

39:04.577 --> 39:09.147
♪

39:09.190 --> 39:13.369
♪ So, it's time
to quit grieving♪

39:13.412 --> 39:15.153
I know.
Hmm.

39:15.196 --> 39:20.506
♪ It's time for believing♪

39:20.550 --> 39:25.859
♪ And it's time
to quit crying♪

39:25.903 --> 39:29.646
♪ Over you♪

39:29.689 --> 39:33.389
♪

39:43.355 --> 39:45.183
[Gun cocks]

39:45.226 --> 39:54.714
♪

39:54.758 --> 39:56.368
We don't want
any trouble.

39:56.412 --> 40:03.331
♪

40:03.375 --> 40:07.074
Well, that makes two of us.

40:07.118 --> 40:09.163
This is our sub.

40:09.207 --> 40:11.165
Last I checked,
the USS Pennsylvaniabelonged

40:11.209 --> 40:14.342
to the Pacific Fleet.

40:14.386 --> 40:16.693
You been following us?

40:16.736 --> 40:18.434
You the one that came with us
on the road?

40:18.477 --> 40:20.827
Look, I said
we don't want any trouble.

40:20.871 --> 40:22.568
And that
sounds like trouble.

40:22.612 --> 40:24.570
Just thought you'd come
and steal from us, is that it?

40:24.614 --> 40:27.834
Morgan.

40:27.878 --> 40:31.316
Morgan Jones?

40:31.359 --> 40:34.580
How do you know that name?

40:34.624 --> 40:36.016
Victor's told us
all about you.

40:36.060 --> 40:38.976
Victor?
Victor's alive?

40:39.019 --> 40:41.805
Oh, very much so.

40:41.848 --> 40:45.722
And here we thought this, uh,
scout was gonna be a bust.

40:48.638 --> 40:52.032
You must be...

40:52.076 --> 40:55.514
Grace.

40:55.558 --> 40:58.038
He's told us
all about you, too.

40:58.082 --> 41:00.301
How would you like to secure
yourself a place in the Tower?

41:00.345 --> 41:01.564
The Tower?

41:01.607 --> 41:04.523
Sorry, Morgan,
you didn't make the cut.

41:04.567 --> 41:07.570
Victor's building a place
removed from the fallout.

41:07.613 --> 41:10.137
Safe from
the world around it.

41:10.181 --> 41:12.575
An ark that will carry us
into the future.

41:12.618 --> 41:14.751
The place
is actually safe?

41:14.794 --> 41:16.883
He's doing everything
you couldn't.

41:16.927 --> 41:19.103
Food, water, security.

41:21.888 --> 41:23.847
What do you say, Grace?

41:23.890 --> 41:26.763
We could use someone
with your expertise.

41:26.806 --> 41:28.373
I know what he did
to Morgan.

41:28.416 --> 41:30.201
I'm not interested
in what he's offering.

41:30.244 --> 41:31.768
I don't want it.You don't have to do that.

41:31.811 --> 41:33.378
Yes, I do.You should think about it.

41:33.421 --> 41:35.206
It's what I want.

41:38.601 --> 41:40.211
He's gonna be disappointed.

41:43.649 --> 41:45.999
Let's go.

41:46.043 --> 41:47.697
Hey, wait. Wait.

41:50.787 --> 41:54.312
Look, Morgan, I already told
you -- you're not welcome.

41:54.355 --> 41:56.053
Okay,
but what about the baby?

41:56.096 --> 41:57.533
Morgan.What about her?

41:57.576 --> 41:59.186
She could use a good home.Morgan, no.

41:59.230 --> 42:00.797
If Victor is building
a place for the future,

42:00.840 --> 42:02.973
he's gonna need people
to live in it, right?

42:03.016 --> 42:10.676
♪

42:10.720 --> 42:11.938
You'd give her up?

42:11.982 --> 42:13.418
I will do whatever's
best for her.

42:13.461 --> 42:15.899
Morgan, no.
She's staying with us.

42:15.942 --> 42:19.076
Whatever Strand's building,
it's not gonna be what we have.

42:19.119 --> 42:21.165
She's right.

42:21.208 --> 42:22.906
It's gonna be better.

42:25.386 --> 42:27.519
It's your only chance, Grace,

42:27.563 --> 42:29.652
for you and the baby.

42:29.695 --> 42:32.480
Victor's memory
is long and sharp.

42:32.524 --> 42:33.569
We're staying.

42:36.267 --> 42:37.529
Suit yourself.

42:37.573 --> 42:45.363
♪

42:45.406 --> 42:53.110
♪

42:53.153 --> 42:55.373
[Mo crying]

42:55.416 --> 43:00.987
♪

43:01.031 --> 43:03.816
Here we go.
Here, here, here.

43:03.860 --> 43:06.863
Oh, they raided
the pantry, too?

43:06.906 --> 43:08.429
Nothing left to take.

43:08.473 --> 43:12.477
[Crying stops]

43:12.520 --> 43:17.525
Wait. If he didn't run us off
the road, who came after us?

43:17.569 --> 43:19.223
I'm not sure.

43:19.266 --> 43:20.746
But we got more
immediate problems.

43:20.790 --> 43:23.140
Mo's gonna be hungry
again soon.

43:28.319 --> 43:30.364
Morgan.

43:30.408 --> 43:32.018
Morgan, look at that.

43:32.062 --> 43:35.761
[Mo babbling]

43:35.805 --> 43:38.677
She's crawling.

43:38.721 --> 43:42.115
We're gonna have to baby-proof
a whole submarine.

43:42.159 --> 43:44.291
Great job, Mo!

43:44.335 --> 43:46.729
[Chuckles]

43:46.772 --> 43:47.991
Morgan.

43:48.034 --> 43:49.819
Morgan, look.

43:49.862 --> 43:52.169
Look at that.
There's something under here.

43:52.212 --> 43:54.475
♪

43:54.519 --> 43:56.521
What the hell?

43:56.564 --> 43:57.653
Lift.

43:57.696 --> 44:04.572
♪

44:04.616 --> 44:06.270
[Both chuckle]

44:06.313 --> 44:08.620
There's enough to last us
for months.

44:08.664 --> 44:09.882
Powdered milk.Powdered milk.

44:09.926 --> 44:11.667
[Laughs]We got powdered milk.

44:11.710 --> 44:14.670
Yeah!
[Chuckles]

44:14.713 --> 44:20.414
♪

44:20.458 --> 44:23.940
[Wind howling]

44:23.983 --> 44:28.945
♪

44:28.988 --> 44:32.165
[Engine shuts off,
car door opens]

44:32.209 --> 44:34.124
[Car door closes]

44:34.167 --> 44:41.958
♪

44:42.001 --> 44:49.792
♪

44:49.835 --> 44:57.582
♪

44:57.625 --> 45:00.846
[Growling]

45:00.890 --> 45:08.419
♪

45:08.462 --> 45:15.905
♪

45:15.948 --> 45:23.521
♪

45:23.564 --> 45:30.963
♪

45:31.007 --> 45:33.183
I'm sorry, brother.

45:33.226 --> 45:37.883
♪

45:37.927 --> 45:40.233
[Inhales shakily]

45:40.277 --> 45:43.628
Mr. Jones may have got
the best of me today...

45:43.671 --> 45:45.673
♪

45:45.717 --> 45:47.893
...but there's always
tomorrow.

45:47.937 --> 45:51.592
♪

45:54.160 --> 45:57.555
♪

45:57.598 --> 46:00.079
You shouldn't be out here
without protection.

46:00.123 --> 46:01.951
Is it really as dangerous
as you said?

46:01.994 --> 46:03.822
I-I-I-I don't know.

46:03.866 --> 46:06.346
I'm done listening to you,
Morgan.

46:06.390 --> 46:08.914
I will come for you,
Victor.

46:09.697 --> 46:10.655
[Gun cocks]

46:11.874 --> 46:12.570
Bring it.

46:12.613 --> 46:17.183
♪

46:17.227 --> 46:18.228
June!

46:18.271 --> 46:23.494
♪

46:24.538 --> 46:31.894
♪

46:31.937 --> 46:34.635
Chambliss: We titled
this episode "Six Hours"

46:34.679 --> 46:38.378
because it is the amount of time
that Grace has calculated

46:38.422 --> 46:40.728
that she and Morgan can be out

46:40.772 --> 46:44.950
before they are exposed to
a dangerous amount of radiation.

46:44.994 --> 46:49.215
It was very important to us,
uh, that this episode

46:49.259 --> 46:53.611
really illustrate just how
devastated the world has been.

46:53.654 --> 46:56.657
I don't ever
want to be here!

46:58.834 --> 47:03.882
This episode really is
about Morgan and Grace

47:03.926 --> 47:08.060
and their very different
viewpoints on being parents

47:08.104 --> 47:12.499
and, specifically, being parents
to baby Mo.

47:12.543 --> 47:15.720
Goldberg: Morgan, as he was
at the end of season six,

47:15.763 --> 47:17.156
is nurturing that baby.

47:17.200 --> 47:19.680
He's the one waking up
and taking care of it.

47:19.724 --> 47:23.032
And you can see
this just haunted look

47:23.075 --> 47:26.078
on Grace's eyes
as she's watching the baby cry.

47:26.122 --> 47:28.864
She is not
emotionally connected.

47:28.907 --> 47:31.910
It was about creating kind of
that sense of tension

47:31.954 --> 47:33.781
and, uh, at the same time,
I think,

47:33.825 --> 47:35.435
start to make the audience
wonder

47:35.479 --> 47:37.394
if there was something more
underneath it,

47:37.437 --> 47:39.657
uh, as we'll later find out.

47:39.700 --> 47:42.921
This episode required
our baby Mo

47:42.965 --> 47:45.619
to do a lot of crying.

47:45.663 --> 47:47.360
[Crying]
Come on.

47:47.404 --> 47:49.014
But there was
no problem there.

47:49.058 --> 47:51.625
In this episode,
the baby is a --

47:51.669 --> 47:53.453
is a fantastic crier.

47:53.497 --> 47:57.762
[Baby crying]

47:57.805 --> 48:01.374
It's an Emmy-worthy performance
from this baby.

48:01.418 --> 48:04.247
Did you find the formula?

48:04.290 --> 48:05.944
No.

48:05.988 --> 48:08.729
I've been working on
something else instead.

48:08.773 --> 48:11.297
We wanted this episode
to start off at a place

48:11.341 --> 48:14.344
of this kind of bizarre take
on a family road trip

48:14.387 --> 48:16.781
through the nuclear apocalypse.

48:16.824 --> 48:19.218
Chambliss:
We started to think about
other apocalyptic fiction

48:19.262 --> 48:21.742
that we're fans of,
and, you know, of course,

48:21.786 --> 48:24.006
"Mad Max" came to mind, and we
thought it would be really cool

48:24.049 --> 48:27.139
to do something that was
kind of a-a nod to that.

48:27.183 --> 48:28.924
It's safe
for all of us.

48:28.967 --> 48:31.578
This vehicle is kind of
hermetically sealed

48:31.622 --> 48:34.059
with duct tape and plastic, um,

48:34.103 --> 48:38.977
and has fuel tanks so they can
drive a long range.

48:39.021 --> 48:41.240
And it also means you need a --
you need a very particular

48:41.284 --> 48:43.199
kind of car seat.

48:43.242 --> 48:46.289
♪

48:46.332 --> 48:48.073
[Gun cocks]

48:48.117 --> 48:50.902
The initial inspiration
Andrew and I had

48:50.946 --> 48:53.296
for Bea and Fred
was "Invisible Man."

48:53.339 --> 48:57.082
And based on some research
we've done on survivors of,

48:57.126 --> 49:00.259
uh, Hiroshima
and other nuclear events,

49:00.303 --> 49:02.870
just seeing, you know,
what long-term effects

49:02.914 --> 49:05.003
of radiation burns
would look like.

49:05.047 --> 49:07.832
They've got her.
She's here. Ohh!

49:07.875 --> 49:10.356
Mommy's here.
Mommy's here.

49:10.400 --> 49:13.794
Chambliss:
Bea and Fred kidnap baby Mo
and are threatening to take her

49:13.838 --> 49:17.233
into what will probably
be her certain death.

49:17.276 --> 49:19.409
It does something for Grace.
I think it starts

49:19.452 --> 49:22.020
to awaken kind of
that maternal instinct.

49:22.064 --> 49:23.935
You're gonna
get her killed.

49:23.979 --> 49:25.502
Never.

49:25.545 --> 49:27.286
For Morgan,

49:27.330 --> 49:29.462
seeing Grace take even
that first step

49:29.506 --> 49:32.161
makes him realize that,
you know, his dream

49:32.204 --> 49:34.990
of having a family again
might not be totally gone.

49:36.600 --> 49:38.776
Goldberg: These two people --
Morgan and Grace --

49:38.819 --> 49:41.779
are able to find a way forward
together with shared purpose,

49:41.822 --> 49:44.303
and, ultimately for Grace,
that's about, uh,

49:44.347 --> 49:47.437
connecting with this baby
in a way that she never
thought she could.

49:47.480 --> 49:49.352
[Cries]

49:49.395 --> 49:50.918
Morgan Jones?

49:50.962 --> 49:52.659
How do you
know that name?

49:52.703 --> 49:55.314
I think we can see from the look
on Morgan's face

49:55.358 --> 49:56.924
when Howard tells him
Victor is alive

49:56.968 --> 49:59.492
that he's not too thrilled.

49:59.536 --> 50:01.494
Chambliss: Both Grace and Morgan
know what Strand did

50:01.538 --> 50:04.062
at the end of season six.
He tried to kill Morgan.

50:04.106 --> 50:06.630
Whatever Strand's building,
it's not gonna be what we have.

50:06.673 --> 50:10.329
She's right.
It's gonna be better.

50:10.373 --> 50:13.854
This moment speaks to
a larger conflict

50:13.898 --> 50:16.074
that's gonna play out over
the course of the season,

50:16.118 --> 50:19.512
which is a bit of
a Morgan versus Strand,

50:19.556 --> 50:22.907
where Strand wants to
shove it in Morgan's face

50:22.950 --> 50:24.474
how much he beat him

50:24.517 --> 50:27.825
and how he's going to do
what Morgan couldn't.

50:27.868 --> 50:32.264
♪

50:32.308 --> 50:34.875
Morgan, look at that.

50:34.919 --> 50:37.269
She's crawling!

50:37.313 --> 50:41.273
And the crawling leads to
the discovery of the food.

50:41.317 --> 50:42.927
What the hell?

50:44.233 --> 50:46.887
God!

50:46.931 --> 50:48.498
They'll always remember
Mo's first crawl

50:48.541 --> 50:50.239
actually kept them alive.

50:50.282 --> 50:51.718
Powdered milk.[Laughs]

50:51.762 --> 50:54.678
We got powdered milk!
Yeah! [Chuckles]

50:54.721 --> 50:57.507
Chambliss:
At the end of the episode,
when we see a figure

50:57.550 --> 51:00.336
walk up to the burnt box
that says "Morgan Jones"

51:00.379 --> 51:02.599
and we see that figure
lift the head up

51:02.642 --> 51:06.298
and we see him take his mask off
and we realize it's Emile's face

51:06.342 --> 51:08.431
looking back at walker Emile,

51:08.474 --> 51:12.826
um, and, uh, we realize that
he actually had a twin brother.

51:12.870 --> 51:17.004
When we cast Demetrius Grosse
in the role of Emile

51:17.048 --> 51:21.052
and we saw his audition and then
we saw his dailies come in,

51:21.096 --> 51:24.751
we knew, you know,
he was an amazing actor

51:24.795 --> 51:27.841
and he really brought something
special to this role.

51:27.885 --> 51:31.106
Man: These are good.
What's in 'em?

51:34.761 --> 51:38.025
A chef never reveals
his secrets.

51:38.069 --> 51:41.420
Besides,
it's my brother's recipe.

51:41.464 --> 51:43.857
We wanted to find a way
to bring this character --

51:43.901 --> 51:47.731
or to bring Demetrius back --
even if it wasn't as Emile.

51:47.774 --> 51:51.778
Mr. Jones may have got
the best of me today.

51:51.822 --> 51:54.085
[Breathes deeply]

51:54.129 --> 51:56.348
But there's always
tomorrow.

51:56.392 --> 51:58.568
We got the chance to do it,
and can't wait

51:58.611 --> 52:01.092
to see what people think
of -- of that episode.

52:01.136 --> 52:06.141
♪

52:08.273 --> 52:17.108
♪

52:17.152 --> 52:26.030
♪

52:26.073 --> 52:35.039
♪
